content: Fortnite Season 6 - What's with the Cube?

tag: html body div div div div article div section p span
content: As of last month, a giant purple Cube entered Fortnite and has been rolling around the map, confusing players as it goes. The bizarre item surely holds the clues to what's coming next in the game...

tag: html body div div div div article div section p span
content: To understand the Cube, you need to understand Fortnite 'lore' so far. It began when a missile launched and tore a rift open in the sky. Then, from the rifts, new areas came to the game and a giant temple celebrating a tomato-based God appeared, too. The Enforcer skin dropped, which hinted at putting a stop to these space/time shenanigans, and the rift began to close.

tag: html body div div div div article div section p span
content: But as it closed, it summoned a sentient Cube. The Cube - which punishes those that shoot at it with deadly bolts of purple lightning - moves every two hours towards an undisclosed destination. Datamined information suggests the Cube is en route to Loot Lake, but as of right now, its motivations and destination remain a mystery.

tag: html body div div div div article div section p span
content: The Cube made its way to Loot Lake and melted, creating a big bouncy lake - and that's where we're at now.

This, paired with the 'Crazy Castle' spray introduced in the game as part of the Season 5 Battle Pass, suggests we may be getting a fantasy/Medieval theme.

tag: html body div div div div article div section p span
